      "raw": "Education\nM.Sc. in Computer Science and Engineering,\nNorth South University, Bangladesh\nB.Sc. in Computer Science and Engineering,\nNorth South University, Bangladesh"
    }
  ],
  "publications_raw": [
    "Journal Articles\nJ. F. Ruma\n, T. T. Mayeesha, and R. M. Rahman, “Transformer based Answer-Aware Bengali Question Generation,”\nInternational Journal of Cognitive Computing in Engineering\n, vol. 4, pp. 314–326, 2023, doi:\nhttps://doi.org/10.1016/j.ijcce.2023.09.003\n.\nJ. F. Ruma\n, F. Anjum, R. Siddiqua, Md. A. Rahman, A. H. Rohan, and R. M. Rahman, “Outdoor patient classification in hospitals based on symptoms in Bengali language,”\nJournal of Information and Telecommunication\n, vol. 7, no. 3, pp. 336–358, Jul. 2023, doi: 10.1080/24751839.2023.2196106.\nJ. F. Ruma\n, M. S. G. Adnan, A. Dewan, and R. M. Rahman, “Particle swarm optimization based LSTM networks for water level forecasting: A case study on Bangladesh river network,”\nResults in Engineering\n, vol. 17, p. 100951, Mar. 2023, doi: 10.1016/j.rineng.2023.100951.\nJ. F. Ruma\n, S. Akter, J. J. Laboni, and R. M. Rahman, “A deep learning classification model for Persian Hafez poetry based on the poet’s era,”\nDecision Analytics Journal\n, vol. 4, p. 100111, Sep. 2022, doi: 10.1016/J.DAJOUR.2022.100111.\nM. Rahaman, Md. M. Hillas, J. Tuba,\nJ. F. Ruma\n, N. Ahmed, and R. M. Rahman, “Effects of Label Noise on Performance of Remote Sensing and Deep Learning-Based Water Body Segmentation Models,”\nCybernetics and Systems\n, vol. 53, no. 6, pp. 581–606, Aug. 2022, doi: 10.1080/01969722.2021.1989171.\nRuma, J. F.\n, Sultana, J., Akter, S., Laboni, J. J., & Rahman, R. M. (2025). Deep learning and Bert-based models for Poetry Analysis: A study on chronological and subject-wise categorization of Tagore’s poetic works.\nSN Computer Science\n,\n6\n(7). https://doi.org/10.1007/s42979-025-04408-0",
    "Conference Proceedings\nHasan, M., Islam, L.,\nRuma, J.,\nMayeesha, T., & Rahman, R. (2023, September). Visual Question Generation in Bengali. In\nProceedings of the Workshop on Multimodal, Multilingual Natural Language Generation and Multilingual WebNLG Challenge (MM-NLG 2023)\n(pp. 10-19)."
